  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (e9f274d 2022-12-11T00:04:59.790449Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nscript\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nTrying out [blacksmith](https://github.com/blacksmith-eth/blacksmith), the tutorial suggests using `forge create`, which works. But verification with `forge script` fails silently.\r\n\r\nTo reproduce:\r\n1. Run a blacksmith and an anvil server\r\n2. `forge init test_verify_fail && cd test_verify_fail`\r\n3. Modify `CounterScript` to deploy the `Counter` contract\r\n4. `forge script CounterScript --verify --unlocked --sender 0xf39fd6e51aad88f6f4ce6ab8827279cfffb92266 --rpc-url http://localhost:8545 --verifier-url http://localhost:3000/api/verify --etherscan-api-key blacksmith --broadcast`\r\n5. The tx is broadcast but no verification occurs.\r\n\r\nNote that the following does verify correctly: `forge create src/Counter.sol:Counter --verify --unlocked --from 0xf39fd6e51aad88f6f4ce6ab8827279cfffb92266 --rpc-url http://localhost:8545 --verifier-url http://localhost:3000/api/verify --etherscan-api-key blacksmith`",
