    "body": "To provide some additional context hereâ€“[blacksmith](https://github.com/blacksmith-eth/blacksmith) relies on the `--verifier-url` flag of `forge create` in order to provide a custom route (e.g. `http://localhost:3000/api/verify`) that accepts the contract source code, compiles it, and stores the ABI (which is used to render contract inputs in the application).\r\n\r\nAt a cursory glance of the `forge script` code, it seems that `clap` accepts all of the `VerifierArgs` defined in `cli/src/cmd/forge/verify/mod.rs`, but the `verifier_url` doesn't seem to be used by `forge script` like it is when verifying with `forge create`.\r\n\r\nI suspect that this isn't just an issue with Blacksmith, but that `forge script` doesn't fully support custom verifier urls.\r\n\r\nAlso, I believe the label here should be updated to `Cmd-forge-script`, and `Cmd-forge-create` should be removed.",
